            <p>POSTAL CARD.<lb/>
                WRITE THE ADDRESS ON THIS SIDE&#8212;THE MESSAGE ON THE OTHER<lb/></p>
            <p>H S Morais Esq.<lb/>
                546 North 5th<lb/>
                Philada.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>244 W 52. 27&#47;9&#47;81<lb/></p>
            <p>H. S. Morais Eq.<lb/>
                My dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your maiden experience required<lb/> a virago&#44; and a virago of unusual masculine vigor.<lb/>  I congratulate you however on your success and regret you should<lb/> be troubled with the throat&#59; there is no fear however of inflammation<lb/> unless you were imprudent in exposure&#59; it is simply due to unaccustomed<lb/> exertion and will wear off especially if you will tend it.<lb/></p>
            <p>I write to <sic>newport</sic> to inquire as to aid&#59; I expected Mr Ginsburg&#39;s brother<lb/> would aid you&#44; he having read service there before on Sat&#39;dy.<lb/>  I have received the &#36;5.<lb/></p>
            <p>I will of course keep you posted as to what is to be done for<lb/> Atonement Day.<lb/></p>
            <p>With kind regards to yr father I am dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;&#63;&#93; H P Mendes.<lb/></p>
        </body>
